FAQs
1. Do I need to know the local language to study medicine in Europe?
Not necessarily. Many universities offer programs in English, but knowing the local language can be beneficial.

2. How do I apply to European medical schools?
Each university has its own application process, usually detailed on their websites. Ensure you meet the eligibility requirements and prepare for any necessary entrance exams.

3. Are there scholarships available for international students?
Yes, many universities and EU programs offer scholarships for international students.

4. What is the cost of living like in Europe?
It varies by country. Western Europe is generally more expensive than Eastern Europe.

5. Can I work part-time while studying?
Yes, most European countries allow international students to work part-time during their studies.
